      "content": "That's a good start for the tone. I want to push the tension a bit more for a specific character, maybe a more radical or \"hardline\" member of the council. If he were speaking to the others, expressing a more aggressive or even dehumanizing view to convince them that any concessions would lead to the total downfall of their way of life, how would he put that? I need the dialogue to feel uncomfortably real for the reader to really feel the stakes of the era.",
